metadata:
  section_id: 6
  section_name: Chapter 6
  hadith_first: 44
  hadith_last: 48

hadiths[5]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
44,"“I came to the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) with a son of mine, so he said; ‘Is this your son?’ I said: ‘Yes,\nI acknowledge him!’ He said: ‘He must not harm you, and you must not harm him!’ I also noticed that the grayness of his hair was reddish.”",,,48759,"Abu Rimtha informed:",Chapter 6
45,"“Did Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) dye ?” He said: “Yes!”",,,48760,"Abu Huraira was asked:",Chapter 6
46,"""I saw Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) come out of his house shaking his head, for he had performed the major ritual ablution, and on his head there was some trace of henna."" (Or he said: saffron. The Shaikh doubted this.)",,,48761,"Al-Jahdama, the wife of Bishr ibn al- Khasasiyya, said:",Chapter 6
47,"""I saw the hair of Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace)dyed.”",,,48762,"Humaid told us that Anas said:",Chapter 6
48,"'Abdullah ibn Muhammad ibn 'Uqail also informed us: ""I saw the hair of Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) dyed in the presence of Anas ibn Malik.""",,,48763,"Hammad said:",Chapter 6
